faces = detector.detect_faces(img_instance)

if faces: 
    print("Face is detected")

# Function to process images (case 2: if face is detected then return face, else keep original version)
def preprocess_image(img_path, target_size):
    img = cv2.imread(img_path)
    
    # Detect faces in the image
    faces = detector.detect_faces(img)
    
    if faces == []: 
        face_img = cv2.resize(img, target_size) 
        face_img = face_img.astype(np.float32) / 255.0
    else: 
        # Extract only the first face detected
        x, y, width, height = faces[0]['box']
        face = img[y:y+height, x:x+width]

        # Process image
        face_img = cv2.resize(face, target_size)
        face_img = face_img.astype(np.float32) / 255.0
    
    return face_img
